description: • CIDNE Operator functioned as a part of an intelligence analytical team consisting of HUMINT analyst, All-Source analyst, and an Intelligence Collection Manager. Performed data entry on relevant IED incidents, personnel, device, or exploitation analysis into the CIDNE system accurately. CIDNE Operator ensured the validity of IED activity data entered into CIDNE and performed quality assurance/quality control analysis of CIDNE data entry process and content. • Navy and Army Special Forces (SOF) liaison assisted with the analysis and production of various intelligence products specifically focused on the C-IED mission at the tactical and operational level related to insurgent IED cell activities, and threats to local/regional stability. Coordinated C-IED Intelligence Surveillance and Reconnaissance (ISR) collection for future operational planning. Provided FMV analysis for future planning and operations for Special Programs. Acted as SOFT-EAST AOB liaison, coordinated collection and intelligence sharing to assist in future operational planning and targeting, also provided daily SIGACT updates. • Conducted Joint Intelligence and Operations with NATO forces and performed liaison tasks with Norwegian, Latvian, and Polish forces. • Functioned as CIAT liaison for Law Enforcement Professional Investigative and Surveillance Unit (LEP-IS). Provided intelligence support and assistance with the role of judicial, biometrics, and criminal intelligence investigation process. • Created Engineer Brigade CIDNE Reporting SOP and training plan. Trained soldiers on proper reporting procedures and functions of CIDNE, WEBTAS, and GEOQUEST for future analysis and operational planning.
